g.text: Entity - An Object we want to model or create information about.
Attributes - Specific pieces of information about the entity
Primary Key - An attribute that uniquely identifies an entry in the database table.
Composite Attribute - An attribute that can be broken down into sub-attributes
Multi-Valued Attribute - An attribute that can have more than one value
Derived Attribute - An attribute that can be derived from other attributes
Multiple Entities - You can have more than one Entity in ER - Diagram
Relationships - Defines a relation between 2 entities
Relationship Attributes - An attribute about the relationship
Relationship Cardinatlity - The number of instances of an entity from a relation can be associated with relation
Weak Entity - An entity that cannot be uniquely identified by its attributes alone
Identifying relationship - A relationship that uniquely identifies a weak entity
Exam is a Weak entity because it cannot exist without class
Simiarly exam ID cannot exist without exam entity
